    "To establish a standardized framework for understanding psychotherapy, we propose a hierarchical taxonomy aligned with the American Psychological Association (APA)'s tripartite model of psychotherapeutic processes foot_0.",
    "As illustrated in Figure 1, this taxonomy organizes psychotherapy into three core components: (1) Assessment, (2) Diagnosis, and (3) Treatment, with dynamic interconnections foot_1.",
    "Each component is detailed below.",
    "Definition.",
    "Psychological assessment constitutes the systematic collection and interpretation of data regarding an individual's cognitive, emotional, and behavioral functioning (Cohen et al., 1996; Kaplan and Saccuzzo, 2001)."
  ]
